by ogizanagi at 2017-08-31T19:41:05Z

Re-opening this one, as the conflict rule looks legit to me though: We don't do a `class_exists` check on `DebugCommand` which is only available as of `symfony/form` 3.4. So Using FrameworkBundle 3.4+ with `symfony/form` 3.3 will raise a:

> PHP Fatal error:  Uncaught Symfony\Component\Debug\Exception\ClassNotFoundException: Attempted to load class "DebugCommand" from namespace "Symfony\Component\Form\Command".

We could tweak the FrameworkExtension, but I think we're already used to bump the min-version by adding a conflict rule in such cases in the FrameworkBundle.

